pageContext.description: A worn fragment of a socketed axe of Late Bronze Age date  (about 1100-800 BC). The fragment consists of the lower blade and cutting  edge. The fragment is broadly rectangular in plan; triangular in profile and has an irregular sub-rectangular cross section. The cutting edge is curved and had slightly projecting tips. The casting seam is visible on the sides of the axe, but have been trimmed and flattened. The socket is 16.54mm deep, while the whole fragment is 35.8mm long. In profile the socket is V shaped. The axe has a smooth brown patina with much damage, and is light green but stable where damaged. The breaks are worn and patinated.
